$ Bash: Shell parameter expansion
@ Shell parameter expansion

{ Substring of a variable

  The substring of a â†’ Linux/shell/bash/variables[variable] can be extracted with `${var:start}` or `${var:start:end}`:
  gh|about-Bash|/expansion/shell-parameter/substring||

}
{ Length of a variable

  The length of a variable can be determined with `${#var}`:
  gh|about-Bash|/expansion/shell-parameter/length||

}
{ Replace/change parts of the variable value

  `${var/pattern/replacement}` returns the value of the variable with `pattern` replaced by `replacement`.
  
  The variable itself does not change.

  gh|about-Bash|/expansion/shell-parameter/replace||

}
